.hy
.TH "" "" "" "" ""
.SH NAME
.PP
enigma.pl
.SH synopsis
.PP
enigma3.pl (pass_options) (options)
.SH description
.PP
This is an enigma emulator.
You configure via the command line or a config file.
.PP
Basic operation entails configuration and data entry.
If the data to be transformed is given on the command line then the
program runs in automatic mode.
Otherwise, enigma3.pl runs as an interactive program.
.SH (options)
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-rotor_file\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
This is used to override the default of \[aq]etc/rotors.txt\[aq].
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-rotors R:R:R\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Specify the rotors in left to right order.
Use Roman numerals (traditional nomenclature).
(default: II:I:III)
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-ring (L:L:L|N:N:N)]\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Specify the ring setting of the rotors.
You can use either the letter (\[aq]A\[aq]) or the number (\[aq]01\[aq])
for the values.
(default: X:M:V)
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-position (L:L:L|N:N:N)]\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Specify the initial position of the rotors.
Follows the same format as for \[aq]ring\[aq].
(default: A:B:L)
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-stecker LL(:LL....)]\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
This specifies the stecker pairs to be used.
Specify as pairs of letters separated by \[aq]:\[aq].
(default: AM:FI:NV:PS:TU:WZ)
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-reflector L\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Specify the reflector to use.
(default is the \[aq]A\[aq] reflector)
.RE
.SH (pass\-through_options)
.PP
these options are passed through to various library calls.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-transitions\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Shows the substition chain; a simple list of letters that show
key\->stecker\->rotor1\->rotor2\->rotor3\->reflector\->rotor3\->rotor2\->rotor1\->stecker\->lamp.
This option just shows those values.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-state_check\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Used to show the initial state of the machine.
Mainly for debugging.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-wiring\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
Shows a simplified ascii graphic of the wiring state of the machine at
that time.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]\-\-\-fancy_wiring\f[]
.RS 2
.PP
This shows a graphic that looks more like the rotor should.
The mapping is kept internal to the rotor.
There are lines that connect one side of the rotor to the other and some
lines that connect the rotors.
.RE
.SH example
.PP
enigma3.pl (nb.
the daily key is FOL but the message key is ABL)
.PP
plaintext : FEIND LIQEI NFANT ERIEK OLONN EBEOB AQTET XANFA NGSUE
.PD 0
.P
.PD
ciphertext: GCDSE AHUGW TQGRK VLFGX UCALX VYMIG MMNMF DXTGN VHVRM
.PP
plaintext : DAUSG ANGBA ERWAL DEXEN DEDRE IKMOS TWAER TSNEU STADT
.PD 0
.P
.PD
ciphertext: MEVOU YFZSL RHDRR XFJWC FHUHM UNZEF RDISI KBGPM YVXUZ
.PP
(example from Frode Weierud\[aq]s Cryptocellar
website (http://cryptocellar.web.cern.ch/cryptocellar/enigma/EMsg1930.html).
.PP
